<h2 id="_general_information_about_elmr">1. General information about Elm@r</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p><strong>Elm@r</strong> (electronic market) is a data standard which was developed in a research project at the University of Mannheim. Since plentymarkets makes use of this standard, item data can easily and automatically be embedded in various product search engines.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="sect1">
<h2 id="_setup">2. Setup</h2>
<div class="sectionbody">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Modifications have to be made in two areas. On the one hand, first level categories have to be linked to the Elm@r categories. On the other hand, general information about the store and its owner have to be saved.</p>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="_linking_categories">2.1. Linking categories</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Category links are carried out for each category in the <strong>Items » Categories » Tab: Settings</strong> menu.</p>
</div>
<div id="image-linking-categories-elmar" class="imageblock">
<div class="content">
<img src="{{plugin_path('PlentyManual')}}/images/omni-channel/online-store/setting-up-clients/extras/assets/EN-Settings-Client-Standard-Services-Elmar-01.png" alt="EN Settings Client Standard Services Elmar 01">
</div>
<div class="title">Figure 1. linking categories with Elm@r</div>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Linking categories with Elm@r:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Item » Categories</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Open the category that you want to link with Elmar.<br>
→ The <strong>Settings</strong> tab is automatically opened when a category is opened.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>From the drop-down list, select the <strong>Elmar category</strong> that you would like to link this category to (<a href="#image-linking-categories-elmar">Figure 1</a>). Please note that these categories are in German, as Elmar is a German data standard.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="_entering_information_about_the_store_and_its_owner">2.2. Entering information about the store and its owner</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In order to generate the shop file (section 2.3), information has to be saved about the store and its owner. To do so, proceed as follows.</p>
</div>
<div id="image-configuring-elmar" class="imageblock">
<div class="content">
<img src="{{plugin_path('PlentyManual')}}/images/omni-channel/online-store/setting-up-clients/extras/assets/EN-Settings-Client-Standard-Services-Elmar-02.png" alt="EN Settings Client Standard Services Elmar 02">
</div>
<div class="title">Figure 2. configuring Elm@r</div>
</div>
<div class="paragraph instruction">
<p>Saving shop data:</p>
</div>
<div class="olist arabic">
<ol class="arabic">
<li>
<p>Go to <strong>Setup » Client » Select client » Services » Elmar</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the data and carry out the settings as desired (<a href="#image-configuring-elmar">Figure 2</a>).</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Under <strong>Item export format</strong> select the file which you saved for Elmar in the <a href="/en/data/export-import/exporting-data">Setup » Markets » Price analysis » Exports</a> menu.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p><strong>Save</strong> the settings.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="admonitionblock warning">
<table>
<tbody><tr>
<td class="icon">
<i class="fa icon-warning" title="Warning"></i>
</td>
<td class="content">
<div class="title">Data validation and security</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>After having been entered, the data will be subject to a test. The security procedure will only be carried out if the test is successful. All data fields need to be filled out correctly and truthfully.</p>
</div>
</td>
</tr>
</tbody></table>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect2">
<h3 id="_generating_the_shop_file">2.3. Generating the shop file</h3>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>All of the information that was given in the <strong>Setup » Client » Select client » Services » Elmar</strong> menu is necessary for generating an XML file. This shop file will be analyzed by Elm@r and its content will be forwarded to product search engines. This file has the name shopinfo.xml and can be accessed via the shop’s URL, e.g. <a href="http://www.my-shop.com/shopinfo.xml" class="bare">http://www.my-shop.com/shopinfo.xml</a></p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The shop file will be automatically updated once a day. If changes are made in the <strong>Setup » Markets » Price analysis » Exports</strong> menu, then the update will take place directly.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>After all information has been entered, the store still has to be registered with <a href="http://www.elektronischer-markt.de/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Elm@r</a>. The <strong>shop file’s URL</strong> is necessary for doing so.</p>
</div>
</div>
